com.github.emabrey.javartmp.core.measurement.length

Class LengthRange

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.emabrey.javartmp.core.measurement.length.LengthRange

  • public class LengthRange
extends Object

    An immutable value class used to represent range-based length information in a compound format containing minimum and maximum scalars alongside an associated length unit. The unit information of the LengthRange class is represented using a value from those enumerated within LengthUnit, which provides implementations of ConvertableLengthUnit to allow exact unit conversions in an extensible manner. The length range information of an instance of LengthRange is represented as an inclusively bounded range between two scalar unsigned longs. This class uses BigInteger internally to maximize mathematical utility in an overflow-aware manner; note that the exact implementation of LengthRange is intended to maximize compiler optimizations via usage of static methods to hopefully avoid some of the associated performance costs.

    Author:
    Emily Mabrey (emabrey@users.noreply.github.com)

        public static LengthRange exactly(long exactLengthScalar,
                                  LengthUnit lengthUnit)

        Convenience method that provides syntatic sugar for generating LengthRange instances via a call to exactly(ULong, LengthUnit) that uses a ULong generated from the provided long value.

        Parameters:
        exactLengthScalar - A long value containing a positive and non-zero value; this is only a lengthUnit-less scalar.
        lengthUnit - The lengthUnit of this LengthRange instance; this lengthUnit qualifies the scalar value.
        Returns:
        A newly created instance of LengthRange that represents the provided scalar as an exact number of the provided lengthUnit.

      • convertedTo

        public LengthRange convertedTo(LengthUnit desiredLengthUnit)

        Generates a new instance of LengthRange which uses the provided LengthUnit to represent the exact same length information represented by this LengthRange instance. The calculation is performed using BigInteger to avoid overflowing the unsigned long type. The final scalar lengths of the newly generated LengthRange may not exceed the maximum value of an unsigned long without generating an exception, however all intermediate calculations avoid conversions and will successfully and temporarily overflow an unsigned long to the extent permitted by BigInteger.

        Parameters:
        desiredLengthUnit - The desired unit of the newly generated LengthRange
        Returns:
        A newly generated LengthRange using the desired lengthUnit to represent the same length information of this LengthRange instance.

      • isExact

        public boolean isExact()

        Indicates if this LengthRange can be represented as a single exact and finite numerical scalar using the current LengthUnit.

        Returns:
        A boolean value of true to indicate that this LengthRange has exactly equal minimum and maximum bounds; false otherwise.
